    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-05-06T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-05-06T04:00:00-05:00" n="713"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d713">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">890D.01/594: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-06T11:00:00+02:00"
                            >May 6, 1942—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 2:18 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>158. Since my 155, May 1, I have seen President of Syria and his Foreign Minister
                    in Damascus. Also Maronite Patriarch in Lebanon. Their response was most
                    encouraging and all agreed when I told them we must forget all personal
                    ambitions and petty political rivalries in order to defeat common foe as quickly
                    as possible.</p>
                <p>Incidentally Spears has not yet heard from London about memo in your April
                        28.<note n="19" xml:id="d713fn19">See telegram No. 57, April 28, 10 p.m., to
                        the Consul General at Beirut, <ref target="#pg_593">p. 593</ref>.</note> I
                    have briefly mentioned to him some of my reasons for preferring not to give it
                    our official support immediately.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
